Stacey Abrams skipping President Biden's speech was a result of a scheduling mix-up, according to the President. He mentioned that he spoke with her and they have a great relationship. When asked about the political risk of pushing for voting rights, President Biden said he risks not saying what he believes, emphasizing the importance of the issue. Regarding the pandemic, the President expressed concern about its global impact and mentioned the federal help provided to states. He stated that he is confident they are on the right track.